{title: Heart's Highway}
{artist: Lefty Frizzel}
{composer: Written by Eddie Miller and Alice Harper}

[C]Through your heart there runs a highway
Where [F]loves traffic comes and [D7]goes
And [G7]the old loves are replaced by the [C]new
I keep searching for the stop sign I [F]know I'll never [D7]find
Cause [G7]I'm just another love passing [C]through
[F]How I'd like to linger  [C]how I'd love to stay
